10 An Act relating to sex offenders; defining terms;
establishing conditions for parole eligibility for
11 certain sex offenders; requiring continuation of
certain treatment to maintain eligibility; stating
12 conditions for revocation of parole; requiring lab
and blood testing; directing the Department of
13 Corrections to promulgate rules; providing immunity
from civil or criminal liability; making provisions
14 of act prospective; amending 57 O.S. 2021, Section
332.21, which relates to parole eligibility;
15 authorizing parole for certain persons; amending 57
O.S. 2021, Section 512, which relates to the
16 supervisions of paroled inmates; providing an
exception for certain defined term; providing for
17 codification; and providing an effective date.
