1 F. The Pardon and Parole Board may grant parole to a prisoner
2 if the Board finds by a preponderance of the evidence that the
3 prisoner, if released, can live and remain at liberty without posing
4 a substantial risk to public safety.
5 G. The Pardon and Parole Board may use the selected evidence-
6 based risk-assessment instrument to make the determination provided
7 for in subsection F of this section.
